                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1358-1">AMS, I, 45-94 ; BHO, 610.
Suhadii ', I, 14- 40.
References dans Vies des saints, VIII, 5 aofit, 86- 87, et BS, VIII, 812- 13 (J.-M. Sauget).
Actes : C. Jullien et F. Jullien, eds. et trads., Les actes de Mar Mari (Louvain, 2004 ;
CSCO 602-603, Scr. syri 234-35) ; et trad. (Turnhout, 2001).
C. Jullien et F. Jullien, Aux origines de l'eglise de Perse : les actes de Mar Mari
(Louvain, 2004 ; CSCO 604, Subsidia 114).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract">Mari was the apostle to Mesopotamia. He was ordained by <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1118">Addai</persName> to establish Christian communities in the royal cities of the Parthians.</note>
                    <note type="disambiguation">with Addai</note>
                    <event type="veneration" source="#bib1358-1">
                        <desc>The saint is venerated on Syr. nestor., feria VI, secundae hebdomadis aestivae. (BHO).</desc>
                    </event>
                    <event type="attestation" xml:id="attestation1358-1" source="#bib1358-1">
                        <p xml:lang="en">Maʾry is commemorated in <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/224">Mari (text)</title>.</p>
                    </event>
